---
globs: content/blog/**/*.md
alwaysApply: false
---
Use the following guidelines to review the blog posts:

- Only make small edits: fix spelling, grammar, and awkward phrasing without changing the author’s voice.
- Keep one main idea per paragraph; split or reorder if several claims are crammed together.
- Define important or unusual terms once in the text so readers don’t have to guess.
- Make cause–effect clear where it matters (e.g. “Because …”, “So …”).
